
Basic Level (1–15)
Check if a number is even or odd.
Find the sum of digits of a number.
Count the number of digits in an integer.
Reverse a given number.
Check if a number is a palindrome.
Check if a number is prime.
Print all prime numbers in a given range.
Find the factorial of a number.
Calculate power (a^b) using loop.
Find the GCD (HCF) of two numbers.
Find the LCM of two numbers.
Check if a number is a perfect number.
Check if a number is an Armstrong number.
Convert a decimal number to binary.
Convert a binary number to decimal.


Intermediate Level (16–30)
16. Convert decimal to octal and hexadecimal.
17. Find all divisors of a number.
18. Check whether a number is a Strong number.
19. Check whether a number is a Happy number.
20. Find the Nth prime number.
21. Find the prime factors of a number.
22. Calculate the product of digits of a number.
23. Check if a number is automorphic (n² ends with n).
24. Print all Armstrong numbers in a given range.
25. Find digital root of a number.
26. Convert a number from any base to decimal.
27. Convert a number from decimal to any base (2 to 16).
28. Count the number of set bits (1s) in binary representation of a number.
29. Find the sum of first N natural numbers.
30. Find the sum of first N odd/even numbers.

Advanced Level (31–40)
31. Find the Nth term of a geometric progression.
32. Find whether a number is a Harshad number (divisible by sum of digits).
33. Print numbers that are both prime and palindrome in a range.
34. Check if a number is a Kaprekar number.
35. Count the number of trailing zeros in a factorial.
36. Find power using fast exponentiation.
37. Check if a number is a circular prime.
38. Generate all Pythagorean triplets with a given sum.
39. Check whether two numbers are co-prime.
40. Check if a number is a Neon number (n² sum of digits = n).